ADDIS ABABA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Africa reached 11,386,362 as of Wednesday evening, the Africa Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) said. The specialized healthcare agency of the African Union (AU) said the death toll across the continent stands at 251,846 and some 10,756,607 patients have recovered from the disease so far. South Africa, Morocco, Tunisia, Egypt and Libya are among the countries with the most cases on the continent, said the Africa CDC. South Africa has recorded the most COVID-19 cases in Africa with more than 3,743,582 cases, followed by Morocco with 1,164,467 cases as of Wednesday evening, it said. In terms of the caseload, southern Africa is the most affected region, followed by the northern and eastern parts of the continent, while central Africa is the least affected region, according to the Africa CDC.  â– 